content.description:
Start about eight feet right of the corner below a right leaning chimney.

Climb a body length up a slabby face then climb out left through the bulge (crux) to the easier, sculpted face above.
content.protection: No gear on the route. You'll need medium cams and at least a cordelette to set up a TR.
content.location: Start about eight feet right of the corner below a right leaning chimney.

content.description:
In the left center of the face is a very obvious left facing corner that leads to a ceiling.

Climb the corner (crux) then move right and up the easier, sculpted face to the top.

If only this route/highball boulder problem were longer...
content.protection:
Smaller cams in the corner, no gear on the face.

Medium cams and at least a cordelette needed to set up a TR.
content.location: In the left center of the face is a very obvious left facing corner that leads to a ceiling.
